body.description: The Ubbi Steel Diaper Pail is made of powder-coated steel to achieve maximum odor control. It is equipped with rubber seals that are strategically designed to lock in odors as well as a sliding lid that minimizes air disruption, keeping the smell inside the pail. To meet the needs of today's parents, this award-winning nursery essential offers the convenience and value of utilizing any standard trash bag or reusable cloth liner. This feature makes it the easiest disposal system to load, use, empty and clean. Offering a modern and sophisticated twist to a once very industrial product, the sleek Ubbi diaper pail includes a child-proof lock and is available in an array of colors. All the style and none of the smell - a promising solution for every nursery. Enter the world of Ubbi where innovative products are designed and created with parents and children in mind. Under the Ubbi name, you will find unique, quality products that are easy to use, helping to simplify parents’ lives while keeping babies as happy and safe as can be. Thanks to its award-winning can of steel, Ubbi is now a recognized brand worldwide. The Ubbi diaper pail is renowned for its ability to achieve maximum odor control and appreciated for offering the convenience and value of utilizing any standard trash bag or reusable cloth liner, a breakthrough in the diaper disposal market. With the same customer focused philosophy and innovative design capabilities, the Ubbi brand is now expanding its signature diapering selection and extending into the feeding category. A wide range of Ubbi branded products is now available for today’s modern parents that are looking for stylish and functional baby essentials. From concept to final creation, the Ubbi team works together every step of the way to bring the best in design and value. The input of every member of the team is taken into account in the development of the Ubbi products, but consumer input is the most important as customer satisfaction is our primary goal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 4, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Got rid of diaper genie
reviews.reviewText: I had been given a diaper genie from a friend. Within 1 week of bringing home baby, my husband insisted the diaper genie was broken and asked me to get something different. The issue with the genie were numerous but the main was the genie was wobbly when trying to pull the bags out, and the bags often tore when replacing.This has solved both problems! Because it’s metal and heavier than the plastic genie, it is sturdier. Additionally, because you can use regular trash bags, we haven’t had any issues with the bags tearing. This is one of my favorite aspects bc it’s 1 less thing to purchase. The capacity also appears to be slightly more. Overall the capacity of diapers on both is somewhat disappointing, as we have to empty it 2-3x a week, and only do about half the diaper changes in the nursery. Although I get the impression we may be going through more diapers on a daily basis than average.I would mention that we have nearly overstuffed it a few times, and I’ve been nervous about ripping the bag. However, if it’s over stuffed, I’ll just tie the bag, and the reach down between can and bag and move some of the diapers up. (The bags we use are always larger than the can since we use the same ones I buy for our kitchen trash.)I have also been very impressed with the smell. We didn’t have the diaper genie long enough for me to comment on smell but I noticed the other day how well this works to keep the smell in, when I opened it to put in a dirty diaper and was overwhelmed by the stink inside! When properly closed you don’t smell anything! However, you will be subject to that stink when changing out the bags.Lastly, I love that it came in colors. The safe green looks adorable in the woodland themed nursery. Being able to get a color was basically just a bonus that put this diaper bin over the top. Would buy again and recommend to friends.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 3, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Pros & Cons A must read
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this Ubbi pail for cat litter waste and here is the results.Pros :The pail is thin and compact and holds a lot of waste. Pretty color and looks nice. Uses regular bags and easy to operate. Lid opening is small which is better to not release a huge amount of stink. It’s almost hard to break the only thing you have to worry about is dings and rust. Being metal it doesn’t absorb stink like plastic can.Cons: You will get a small bit of stink when lid is open while that is common, it says to only use a rag to clean it and after you can still smell stink. So rather hard to clean to get smell off of it. If I’m just using a rag how is that going to clean it ?It can rust. If any contents you put inside are damp it will rust, you need damp rid or silica gel packs inside to absorb any moisture! The opening is small, while it’s great stink wise , it could be a litter bigger to accommodate adult diapers or other uses as for pets. I had to get a skimmer for a pet scoop something small enough to fit. The slide door under can get dirty & hard to clean.Overall it’s good. Definitely not perfect and far from it . It does require maintenance so it’s not maintenance free.I chose this one before the pet version because the pet version while it has a bigger opening it Doesn’t have the slide opening like this one.I use a magnetic hook with a opening teabag ball filled with silica packets to absorb moisture. I also hang a car air freshener inside .But overall I give it a 4. It could last years if you care for it weekly.
